<DOC><DOCNO> AP900404-0230 </DOCNO><FILEID>AP-NR-04-04-90 1927EDT</FILEID><FIRST>u f AM-Sandamp;L-Inquiries     04-04 0134</FIRST><SECOND>AM-Sandamp;L-Inquiries,0139</SECOND><HEAD>Sandamp;L Agency Adopts New Policy on Inquiries</HEAD><DATELINE>WASHINGTON (AP) </DATELINE><TEXT>   The government agency charged with selling offfailed savings and loans has adopted a policy requiring itsemployees to maintain a log of all telephone inquiries made by oron behalf of public officials.   The Resolution Trust Corp. action was announced Wednesday inresponse to policy directives in the Sandamp;L bailout legislationenacted by Congress last summer.   The RTC action also calls for establishment of a specialcommittee which will conduct formal reviews when RTC employesbelieve they have received inappropriate requests from publicofficials.   It also outlined procedures for meetings between RTC employes,public officials and their constituents including a requirementthat such meetings be attended by two or more RTC employees, one ofwhom must be a senior-level employee.</TEXT></DOC>